Based on the challenge description provided, here is the solution:

1. The "1810 London Hoax" This refers to the famous Berners Street Hoax, where Theodore Hook managed to summon hundreds of people (including the Lord Mayor of London) to a single address at 54 Berners Street.

2. The "Culprit" The perpetrator of this prank was Theodore Hook.

3. The "Semi-autobiographical Novel" Theodore Hook later fictionalized and confessed to the details of this hoax in his book titled Gilbert Gurney.

